        "theory": "## Welcome to Go\nGo (Golang) is a statically typed, compiled language designed at Google.\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport \"fmt\"\n\nfunc main() {\n    fmt.Println(\"Hello, World!\")\n}\n```\n\n- `package main`: Tells the compiler this is an executable\n- `import \"fmt\"`: Imports the formatting package (I/O)\n- `func main()`: The entry point of the program",
