        "title": "Generator Pipeline",
        "theory": "## Chaining Generators\nGenerators can be chained to create data processing pipelines.\n\n```python\ndef read_data():\n    for i in range(100):\n        yield i\n\ndef filter_even(data):\n    for item in data:\n        if item % 2 == 0:\n            yield item\n\ndef square(data):\n    for item in data:\n        yield item ** 2\n\n# Pipeline: generate -> filter -> transform\npipeline = square(filter_even(read_data()))\nfor val in pipeline:\n    if val > 50:\n        break\n    print(val)  # 0, 4, 16, 36\n```",
