        "theory": "## Asynchronous Programming\n`async/await` lets you write non-blocking code for I/O-heavy operations.\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\n\nasync def greet(name, delay):\n    await asyncio.sleep(delay)\n    print(f'Hello, {name}!')\n\nasync def main():\n    await greet('Alice', 1)\n    print('Done!')\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n```\n\n`async def` defines a coroutine. `await` pauses until the result is ready.",
